India's youngest martyr definitely deserves more recognition.Salute one of greatest child

name: Virender Sehwag
text: , but he rose again gathering whatever little strength and courage was left with him, and raising his voice to the highest pitch beyond even his strength, warned the British troops not to ferry them till alive. A soldier pierced his bayonet into the soft skull of Baji,

name: Virender Sehwag
text:
The troop threatened to kill him if he did not ferry them across immediately. Baji however rejected their orders.
One of the British soldiers hit Baji's head with his gun butt that fractured his skull severely‚Äã.
Baji collapsed,

name: Virender Sehwag
text: Baji who had already heard details of the brutality of the troop which had killed innocent people in the village understood if the British troops were to be obstructed,then they needed to be stopped from going across to the other bank. He therefore refused to ferry them across

text:

name: Virender Sehwag
text:
Sir Don Bradman on seeing Dhyan Chand said, ‚ÄúYou score goals like runs‚Äù.
Such a legend needs to be known and celebrated so much more.

name: Virender Sehwag
text: During 1936 Olympics, the whole city of Berlin had posters: ‚ÄúVisit the hockey stadium to watch the Indian magician Dhyan Chand in action.‚Äù

name: Virender Sehwag
text: It is said that in the 1936 Berlin Olympics, Dhyan Chand who was the flag-bearer,¬†refused to salute Adolf Hitler.¬†What a man !

name: Virender Sehwag
text:
Barefoot, he scored 3 goals.What a legend !In Netherlands,once
the authorities broke his hockey stick to check if there was a magnet inside.

name: Virender Sehwag
text: During the1936 Olympic final against Germany, it‚Äôs said that Dhyan Chand¬†removed his spiked shoes¬†& stockings in 2nd half & played barefoot

name: Virender Sehwag
text: He was called Chand by his team-mates because he used to wait for the moon to come out for practice. He was also called¬†as "The Wizard"

name: Virender Sehwag
text: Every child in the country must know about the legend Major Dhyanchand was.He joined the Indian army at the age of 16 and retired in 1956.
